For example, Carmel, California has seen inventory of homes priced over $1 million drop 76 percent.

Similar inventory has fallen 70 percent year-over-year in Palm Beach, Florida and is down 58 percent year-over-year in Old Greenwich, Connecticut. 

The California market, especially areas like Carmel and Pebble Beach, have seen a rush of buyers from Silicon Valley, Europe and Asia. 

‘We are seeing an influx of luxury second home buyers coming into the market including venture capitalists, tech money, oil and gas, developers and CEO's,’ said Tim Allen, of Tim Allen Properties in Pebble Beach, told CNBC.

